Indy Criterium Cycling Race & Festival
description:
Situated in the heart of Downtown Indianapolis, the Indy Criterium offers cyclists a unique opportunity to race the city streets that they would rarely do otherwise.  Back by popular demand, racers can anticipate the same figure-8 course!

* $6,050 CASH prize purse
* $1,500 in CASH primes
* Over $4,000 in MERCHANDISE prizes
* Fast, accurate results 
* Podium ceremony on stage - all categories
* Call-ups for first 20 pre-registered in each category
* FREE swag for racers 
* Juniors Regional Championship Races
course: Flat, smooth, wide course in urban downtown Indy setting. 9 turns - 0.95 course length
notes: Held under USA Cycling permit. All USA Cycling rules apply. Free-lap rule is in effect. Lapped riders may be pulled at the officials discretion. You must present a valid 2014 USA Cycling license at registration to enter any race. Only Category 5 men and Category 4 women may purchase a one-day license for $10 at registration. Promoter reserves the right to shorten, modify, cancel or combine any race or prize list in the event of insufficient entries or bad weather. Junior women age 15-18 Cat 4 & Cat 1/2/3 riders will be placed in their respective juniors races and also in the overall category but will be paid from the prize purse of the category in which they registered (juniors), not the overall prize purse. All winners must be present to receive prizes/awards. Day of race registration opens at 8:00am and closes 30 minutes before the start of each race. $20 fee for each additional race. Pre-registration closes at 1159pm EST on 7/9/14. $10 late fee applies for race day registration. Helmets required. No refunds.

title: July 2014 Cycling Skills Clinic
description:
This will be a 4 hour hands on skills clinic - these are skills relevant to all cyclists, no matter if you are a racer or a recreational rider.

Included will be cornering,U turns, more effective bunny hopping

What to do in case of wheel overlap or other contact

Bike to Bike contact will occur so plan your equipment selection accordingly

This clinic is taught by USA Cycling Certified Level 2 & 3 coaches
course: We will be in protected parking lots and grass fields at the event address
notes: Please be sure to sign our online waiver before the event to save time on your checkin. Under 18 must have parent or guardian signature to participate and must contact the race director in advance at 317-750-5607
directions:
Exit On Emerson Ave - Beach Grove exit from I-465 in Indianapolis
- go North on Emerson
- go right on Elmwood (East)
- go left on Elmwood Court
- follow to the end

Fort Wayne Outfitters Bike Depot Cyclecross Series
description: Fort Wayne Outfitters Wednesday Night Cycle-Cross Race Series
course: Cycle cross around the Bike Depot, roughly 1.2 miles. Great Course
registration: $7 to cover insurance cost and permit fees (14 dates) $100 if you want to pay in full for the whole series.
notes:
From 5:00 to 6:00 everyone is invited to come out and warm up and get ready to race at 6:00. This is also a good time to work with the area experts on the fundamentals of Cyclocross racing. We will begin racing at 6 pm and, depending on the size and skill level, will make two or three groups if necessary. We will race for approximately an hour and then allow one 
hour for cool down and also additional technical skills time for people who cant come early. 
 
Schedule: 
5:00-6:00 Warm up and course review, Beginners Clinic 
6:00 A Race, B Race, and C Racing Starts 
7:00-8:00 Cool Down and technical skills train
directions:
Fort Wayne Outfitters and Bike Depot 
1004 Cass Street 
Fort Wayne, IN 46808
